  abstract = {The giant dipole resonance (GDR) built on highly excited states is an important experimental tool in understanding the properties of hot nuclei. A new generation of experiments allows a more detailed study of the dependence of the GDR on temperature and spin. We review the macroscopic theory of the GDR at finite temperature, which is based on a mean-field theory and an exact treatment of thermal shape fluctuations. The systematics of the GDR width as a function of temperature, spin and mass is discussed and compared with experimental data.}
}


