  abstract = {The giant-dipole resonance (GDR) in rapidly rotating hot nuclei is calculated at constant spin by projection from the GDR response function at constant angular velocity. The theory is applied to the Jacobi phase transition of a hot rotating liquid drop and the GDR is found to be a sensitive signature of the transition. Comparison with recent experiments on 45 Sc confirm a Jacobi phase transition from oblate to almost prolate shapes with large deformation.},
